8. Specific Considerations & Knowns
Mobile Camera Flow: The /mobile-camera route is a dedicated mobile-first interface. It uses JWTs for secure session passing and Supabase Realtime for live communication between the mobile device and the desktop application during document scanning. A persistent MOBILE_AUTH_FLOW_ACTIVE_FLAG in localStorage ensures continuity across redirects.
Password Reset Flow: The AuthGuard and ResetPassword components implement strict measures to prevent navigation during a password reset, ensuring the user completes the process securely. It uses localStorage flags (passwordResetFlowActive, blockModalsDuringReset) and global sign-out (supabase.auth.signOut({ scope: 'global' })) to enforce this.
Admin Privileges: Admin status (is_admin in profiles table) is checked in AdminGuard and within most admin-related Edge Functions to enforce access control.
Data Retention: Contracts and analysis results for single-use purchases are automatically deleted after 30 days by the delete-old-files scheduled Edge Function. Subscription users retain files for the duration of their active subscription plus a grace period.
Error Handling: A global ErrorBoundary component is implemented to catch and display unexpected UI errors gracefully.
Theming: The application supports light, dark, and system themes, configurable by the user and applied via document.documentElement.classList.
File Upload Limits: The maxFiles and max_users properties in stripe_subscriptions and stripe_product_metadata are used to enforce plan-specific limits.
Caching: cached_clause_analysis table is used to cache LLM responses for repeated clause analysis.
